author: Bob Shwalb
title: Passaic County tennis tournament postponed to Monday - High School Sports
text:
Rain has continued to wreak havoc on this year’s Passaic County Girls Tennis Tournament.
Buy this photo RECORD FILE PHOTO The final round scheduled for Friday was postponed to Monday due to the weather. It will be contested at Wayne Valley at 3 p.m.
Twelve-time defending champion Wayne Hills finished Thursday’s semifinals with a 14-13 lead over West Milford, which is vying for its first title since 1994 and its fourth overall.
The tournament originally was scheduled for Sept. 29 and 30, but was postponed due to rain.
